{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Strengthen and enforce rules to stop scam emergency trade call-out adverts",
        "additional_details": "We\u2019ve been told the Online Safety Act (OSA) 2023 already requires search engines and platforms to prevent paid-for fraudulent adverts and remove them when reported. But it isn\u2019t working. Rogue emergency trade adverts still appear at the top of search results, pushing reputable local businesses out of view. Complaints keep rising and recent BBC coverage shows the scale of harm. \u201cBait and switch\u201d pricing (cheap advert, inflated bill) misleads consumers in emergencies and is still happening.",
        "background": "Require search engines to verify emergency trade advertisers before allowing paid adverts. Only allow adverts from trusted, accountable providers and ban \u201cbait and switch\u201d pricing. Remove scam adverts quickly and stop repeat offenders from returning.",
